Params: {3: 'Deep in the cosmos, stars scatter across the infinite void.'}
{1: '1', 2: 'Nanami', 3: 'Eeekâ€”that tunnel was super dark and dead silent! Nanami felt super creeped out!', 4: '1'}
{3: 'Nanami shrugs and inputs the commands for another simulation into the terminal.'}
{2: 'Nanami', 3: "Construction complete! Here's hoping this world turns out a bit more normal!", 4: '1'}
{2: 'Was that world we just saw also one of the simulated futures?', 3: '12', 4: 'Onward.', 5: '26'}
{3: 'Nanami turns the screen of "The Big Eater" toward herself. The large display flickers with a dense grid of dots, resembling a galaxy adorned with countless stars.'}
{1: '1', 2: 'Nanami', 3: 'Let\'s call where we are now the Starting Station. From here, we can use "The Big Eater" to enter all kinds of simulated worlds.', 4: '1'}
{3: 'Nanami extends her index finger and touches one of the grid points. In an instant, countless golden lines burst across the screen, weaving themselves into a brand-new grid.'}
{3: 'She swipes the screen to the right, and half of the grid instantly dims before shattering into chaotic streams of data that fade into nothingness.'}

{1: '1', 2: 'Nanami', 3: 'After our recent adventure just now, "The Big Eater" has filtered out these bad endings. In the upcoming simulations, we\'ll avoid Dimension Domains similar to those.', 4: '1'}
{2: 'Nanami', 3: 'This way, "The Big Eater" can save a lot of computing power, and Nanami can be even more powerful during the simulations!', 4: '1'}
{2: 'Nanami', 3: 'Mm-hmm! Nanami, launching in Knight Mode with a 400% combat power boost!', 4: '1'}
